AGED TWENTY SIX, VIGENERE WAS SENT TO ROME ON A DIPLOMATIC MISSION. IT WAS HERE THAT HE BECAME ACQUAINTED WITH THE WRITINGS OF ALBERTI, TRITHEMIUS AND PORTA, AND HIS INTEREST IN CRYPTOGRAPHY WAS IGNITED. FOR MANY YEARS, CRYPTOGRAPHY WAS NOTHING MORE THAN A TOOL THAT HELPED HIM HIS DIPLOMATIC WORK, BUT AT THE AGE OF THIRTY NINE, VIGFNERE DECIDED THAT HE HAD AMASSED ENOUGH MONEY TO BE ABLE TO ABANDON HIS CAREER AND CONCENTRATE ON A LIFE OF STUDY. IT WAS ONLY THEN THAT HE BEGAN RESEARCH INTO A NEW CIPHER.
